  "prompt": "Personal Productivity: Is there a service that allows bookmarking of quotes?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several services and tools that allow you to bookmark and save quotes. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Evernote**: You can create notes specifically for quotes and tag them for easy searching later. \n\n2. **Notion**: Similar to Evernote, Notion allows you to create a database of quotes that you can organize and categorize.\n\n3. **Pinterest**: While primarily a visual bookmarking platform, you can pin images with quotes or create boards dedicated to quotes.\n\n4. **Medium**: You can highlight and save quotes from articles you read on Medium for easy reference.\n\n5. **Quotable**: This is a specialized tool designed for saving and sharing quotes, allowing you to categorize and compile your favorite quotes.\n\n6. **Google Keep**: A simple note-taking app where you can save quotes as notes and categorize them with labels.\n\n7. **Pocket**: Primarily for saving articles, you can also save quotes you find in those articles and highlight them.\n\n8. **Quote Garden**: A website dedicated to quotes where you can save and categorize your favorite quotes.\n\nThese tools not only allow you to save quotes but also offer various features for organization and sharing. Choose one that best fits your workflow and preferences!",
